            <fr:title text="Stalk for structural sheaf">Stalk for structural sheaf</fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>Remark</fr:taxon>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
            <html:p>
  If <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathcal {O}_{D}]]></fr:tex> is a sheaf, then at each prime filter <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[x\in \operatorname {Spec} D]]></fr:tex>, the stalk of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathcal {O}_{D}]]></fr:tex> at <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[x]]></fr:tex> is given by
  <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[ \mathcal {O}_{D,x} \cong  \operatorname {colim}_{p\in  x}D/p \cong  D/x. ]]></fr:tex>
  As a distributive lattice this is <fr:link href="/idem-comm-75C1/" title="Local distributive lattice" uri="https://www.my-great-forest.net/idem-comm-75C1/" display-uri="idem-comm-75C1" type="local">local</fr:link> by <fr:link href="/idem-comm-EV8L/" title="Quotient of prime filters are local" uri="https://www.my-great-forest.net/idem-comm-EV8L/" display-uri="idem-comm-EV8L" type="local">Proposition <fr:contextual-number uri="https://www.my-great-forest.net/idem-comm-EV8L/" display-uri="idem-comm-EV8L" /></fr:link>.
</html:p>
          </fr:mainmatter>
        </fr:tree>
        <fr:tree show-metadata="true" expanded="false" toc="false" numbered="false">
          <fr:frontmatter>
            <fr:authors />
            <fr:date>
              <fr:year>2025</fr:year>
              <fr:month>6</fr:month>
              <fr:day>8</fr:day>
